## ðŸ›°ï¸ Wireshark (Hands-On)

### ðŸ§ª What I Did:
- Captured live network packets
- Applied filters to inspect:
  - Specific protocols (`http`, `tcp.port == 80`)
  - Communication between IPs (`ip.addr == 192.168.X.X`)
- Followed full **TCP streams** to view complete conversations (e.g., login attempts, HTTP requests)
- Used **Endpoints tab** to:
  - Identify active IPv4/IPv6 addresses
  - Analyze communication flows
  - View packet/byte stats per endpoint
- Explored **Statistics > Protocol Hierarchy** and **IO Graphs** for traffic trends and breakdowns

